subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Fig. 5E
). Uncus triangle, apically blunt; gnathos arms short, thick; gnathos small, poorly sclerotized; valve basally sclerotized, caudal end membranous, lanceolately narrowing, stepped bending on the costal edge of the valve (in medium third); transtilla process short, basally very wide, apically narrowing, apex semicircular; juxta tiny, with a pair of short rod-shaped lateral processes; saccus semicircular, robust; phallus equal to 3/4 of valve length, thin, apically narrowing, strongly bent in the medium third, vesica aperture in dorso-apical position, equal to 2/3 of phallus length, vesica without cornuti.
